Bowie）在他的“ Ziggy Stardust”时代和70年代的性手枪的史蒂夫·琼斯（Steve Jones）演出" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie-jones@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie-jones@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie-jones@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie-jones@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie-jones@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie-jones@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sex-pistols">性手枪</a>的史蒂夫·琼斯（Steve Jones）回忆起<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/david-bowie">大卫·鲍伊（David Bowie）</a>的偷窃设备，并在火星表演中的锯齿状星尘和蜘蛛之后。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sex-pistols-steve-jones-interview-teenage-cancer-trust-frank-carter-john-lydon-alex-turner-3832074">性手枪的史蒂夫·琼斯（Steve Jones）告诉我们有关青少年癌症信任的演出，并取消了亚历克斯·特纳（Alex Turner）的写作会议</a></strong></li></ul><p>吉他手分享了轶事，作为与<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2025/mar/30/sex-pistols-steve-jones-q-and-a-interview-10-questions" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>《卫报》</em></a>的新采访的一部分，在那里他回顾了他职业生涯中一些最令人难忘的时刻。</p><p>在讨论中，琼斯被问到谣言流传，说他曾经在1973年从鲍伊（Bowie）偷走了一些音乐设备 - 大约在音乐偶像在伦敦的Hammersmith Odeon演奏的那一部分，这是他上一次Ziggy Stardust展示的一部分。</p><p>他告诉The Outlet：“这肯定有一个道理。它不是在卡车上 - 它在舞台上。” “他们玩了两个晚上，在第一个晚上，他们把所有的装备都留下来，因为第二天晚上在那儿玩。”</p><p>他补充说：“我知道像手的背面一样，我一直在那儿铺位。 “大约是两个早上。我偷了一小千万，我上了。那里没有人，除了一个坐在第四或第五排的家伙，睡着了 - 他打s-打s。</p><p> “我在舞台上tip脚，我划了一些贝斯手的[放大器]头的cymbals  - 一个阳光放大器，还有一些麦克风。我用唇膏上的口红拿到了鲍伊的麦克风！” </p><figure id="attachment_3850947" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3850947" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3850947" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie@2000x1270.jpg" alt="大卫·鲍伊（David Bowie）在1973年的“ Ziggy Stardust”时代演出" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bowie@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3850947" class="wp-caption-text">大卫·鲍伊（David Bowie）在1973年的“ Ziggy Stardust”时代表演。</figcaption></figure><p>当被问及他是否曾经告诉鲍伊在晚上的举动时，琼斯回答说：“我有点打个电话。他知道我做了；他认为这很有趣。实际上，我不认为我把任何东西都划分了，我不认为麦克风是他的。</p><p>他补充说：“实际上，我确实与伍迪做了修改。几年前，他来到我的广播节目中，我想我会告诉他，当我们上空时，我做了什么，我做了什么。我当时想，&#39;我必须对你做修改，伍迪，我刻痕了你的一些cy脚。我可以做什么才能做什么？&#39;&#39;他说：“我不知道；我想我给了他300美元（232英镑），所以他很高兴。”</p><p>至于最近的史蒂夫·琼斯（Steve Jones）新闻，这位吉他手最近再次与他的性手枪的乐队成员和新主持人<a href="https://nme-next.netlify.app/artists/frank-carter">弗兰克·卡特（Frank Carter）</a>合作，参加了今年的《 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-who-the-sex-pistols-and-frank-carter-james-arthur-the-corrs-and-more-to-headline-teenage-cancer-trust-2025-at-royal-albert-hall-3832149">少年癌症信托基金会现场表演》</a> 。</p><p>乐队于上周一（3月24日）与琼斯，卡特，保罗·库克和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/glen-matlock">格伦·马特洛克（Glen Matlock）</a>一起登上了2025年的分期付款，此前<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-molotovs">莫洛托夫斯（Molotovs）</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kid-kapichi">基德·卡皮奇（Kid Kapichi）</a>开幕式。 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sex-pistols-frank-carter-royal-albert-hall-london-teenage-cancer-trust-watch-video-photos-setlist-3849152"><em>NME</em>参加了演出</a>，并回顾了弗兰克·卡特（Frank Carter）和公司（Frank Carter and Co）如何提供爆炸性的表演，其中包括“尸体”，“骗子”，“骗子”和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/iggy-and-the-stooges">iggy and the stooges&#39;classic&#39;no</a> no Fun&#39;的封面。 </p><figure id="attachment_3832394" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3832394" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3832394" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Frank-Carter-Steve-Jones.jpg" alt="Frank Carter and Steve Jones of the Sex Pistols" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Frank-Carter-Steve-Jones.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Frank-Carter-Steve-Jones-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Frank-Carter-Steve-Jones-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Frank-Carter-Steve-Jones-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Frank-Carter-Steve-Jones-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Frank-Carter-Steve-Jones-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3832394" class="wp-caption-text"> Frank Carter and Steve Jones of the Sex Pistols. CREDIT: Jim Dyson/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> Ahead of the gigs, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sex-pistols-steve-jones-interview-teenage-cancer-trust-frank-carter-john-lydon-alex-turner-3832074">the guitar icon caught up with <em>NME</em></a> and discussed the band&#39;s future with Carter, the impact of <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/danny-boyle">Danny Boyle</a> &#39;s &#39;Pistol&#39; biopic, US politics and more.</p><p> When asked whether the members expected the hugely positive response to Carter joining the line-up, he said: “None of us knew. Frank was the first singer we [tried], because me, Cookie and Glen wanted to play. It just worked straight away. He&#39;s a lot younger than us. He&#39;s 40, so he has all that energy and us old farts can just jam at the back!”</p><p> “It was so much fun and people loved it, and I loved looking at people loving it,” he added. “I was ready to throw it in, touring and all that. I couldn&#39;t care less. But with Frank, it just made it easy. We all get along. There&#39;s no aggro. It&#39;s just fun!”</p><p> Explaining what he thought of any naysayers discussing the comeback, he added: “ <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/john-lydon">John [Lydon</a> , former frontman] ain&#39;t interested in doing it. You think you&#39;re gonna get a negative thing by doing [it without him], but I&#39;m surprised. There was no backlash whatsoever.</p><p> “There were a few die-hards on Instagram, but they hadn&#39;t even seen us. They just can&#39;t see it without John, which I get, but even the ones that came out of curiosity were into it after a couple of songs.”</p><p> As for the remainder of 2025, the band <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sex-pistols-and-frank-carter-announce-2025-north-american-tour-3850210">announced details of a 2025 North American tour</a> just last week, with live shows set to kick off later this autumn. <a href="https://ticketmaster.evyy.net/c/2862475/264167/4272?sharedid=NME&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ticketmaster.com%2Fsex-pistols-tickets%2Fartist%2F874727" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit here</a> for remaining tickets.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sex-pistols-steve-jones-on-david-bowies-reaction-after-stealing-equipment-from-ziggy-stardust-the-spiders-from-mars-3850937">Sex Pistols&#39; Steve Jones on David Bowie&#39;s reaction after stealing equipment from Ziggy Stardust &amp; The Spiders From Mars</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
